      "id": "PopularPost159124",
      "post_content": "@ majinara - Wizards didn't run out of ideas, this was *exactly* the idea they were going for. It fits the more brutal theme of Phyrexia very well, and is a griefer counterspell in a griefer set. The whole cycle flavorfully falls in to what they call the \"Phyrexian Blood Tax\" theme - read about it somewhere on the New Phyrexia information page or FAQ, one of the two.",
      "posted_by": "Magnor_Criol",
